<longdescription lang="en">
	urr is a lightweight, dependency-free Wake-on-LAN (WoL) utility written in C.
	Unlike simple WoL tools, urr allows you to manage a database of machines, letting you wake them up using friendly hostnames instead of memorizing 17-character MAC addresses.

The name urr comes from the Hebrew imperative עוּר, meaning "wake up!" or "arise!".
</longdescription>
